      {"type":"explanation","heading":"The Agency Problem","body":"The separation of ownership (shareholders) from control (directors) creates an agency problem. Directors may pursue their own interests rather than maximising shareholder wealth.","key_terms":[{"term":"Principal","definition":"The party on whose behalf the agent acts (shareholders)."},{"term":"Agent","definition":"The party acting on behalf of the principal (directors/managers)."},{"term":"Agency costs","definition":"Costs of monitoring agents and resolving conflicts (e.g. audit fees, incentive schemes)."},{"term":"Agency problem","definition":"Directors may prioritise personal gain over shareholder value."}]},
