      {"type":"explanation","heading":"Types of Internal Control","body":"Internal controls fall into two broad categories: preventive (stop errors/fraud occurring) and detective (identify errors/fraud after they occur).","key_terms":[{"term":"Preventive controls","definition":"Segregation of duties, authorisation limits, password controls, physical access restrictions."},{"term":"Detective controls","definition":"Bank reconciliations, internal audit, exception reports, variance analysis."},{"term":"Segregation of duties","definition":"No single individual controls all stages of a transaction."}]},
